# Bash Cleaner Script 

This is a simple Bash script to clean up unnecessary files (like `.tmp`, `.log`, and `.bak`) from a specified directory. It supports a **dry run** mode to preview which files would be deleted.
this cleaner is for educational purpose and for simple use also.
## Features

- Deletes files with `.tmp`, `.log`, and `.bak` extensions
- Optional `--dry-run` mode to preview files before deletion
- Simple and portable â€” works on any system with Bash

##  Usage

copy the bash file in the target file
run the command ./cleaner.sh --dry-run
